{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/kubernetes/164clusterroles/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Cluster Roles and Role Bindings","date":"May 23, 2024"},"html":"<p>Roles and Role Bindings are namespaced, meaning they are created within namespaces. If a namespace isn't specified, then they are created in the default namespace and control access only within that namespace.</p>\n<p>As a reminder, namespaces help grouping or isolating resources like pods, deployments or services.</p>\n<p>However, what about resources like nodes (blue squares in the right)? Is it possible for them to be in a namespace?</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 28.500000000000004%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"alt text\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/f4867bfc7c24d7d0e9b18bb08a73ce9d/5a190/namespaces.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/f4867bfc7c24d7d0e9b18bb08a73ce9d/772e8/namespaces.png 200w,\n/static/f4867bfc7c24d7d0e9b18bb08a73ce9d/e17e5/namespaces.png 400w,\n/static/f4867bfc7c24d7d0e9b18bb08a73ce9d/5a190/namespaces.png 800w,\n/static/f4867bfc7c24d7d0e9b18bb08a73ce9d/c1b63/namespaces.png 1200w,\n/static/f4867bfc7c24d7d0e9b18bb08a73ce9d/29007/namespaces.png 1600w,\n/static/f4867bfc7c24d7d0e9b18bb08a73ce9d/b6e50/namespaces.png 1862w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<p>The answer is no, nodes are not able to be isolated within a namespace. Instead, they are clusted-wide or cluster-scoped resources. This means that they are accessible from any namespace within the cluster.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 39.49999999999999%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"no\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/22894dc9e62ca6e3ea960aa47e563795/5a190/notpossible.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/22894dc9e62ca6e3ea960aa47e563795/772e8/notpossible.png 200w,\n/static/22894dc9e62ca6e3ea960aa47e563795/e17e5/notpossible.png 400w,\n/static/22894dc9e62ca6e3ea960aa47e563795/5a190/notpossible.png 800w,\n/static/22894dc9e62ca6e3ea960aa47e563795/c1b63/notpossible.png 1200w,\n/static/22894dc9e62ca6e3ea960aa47e563795/29007/notpossible.png 1600w,\n/static/22894dc9e62ca6e3ea960aa47e563795/2ed34/notpossible.png 1776w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<p>In other words, resources can be categorized as either namespaced or cluster-scoped.</p>\n<p>Examples of namespaced resources include pods, replicasets, deployments, and services.</p>\n<p>Examples of cluster-scoped resources includes nodes, persistent volumes, and namespaces.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 39.49999999999999%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"NSvsCluster\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/eeccf579d1262b683b0e39adc7228c26/5a190/nsvscluster.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/eeccf579d1262b683b0e39adc7228c26/772e8/nsvscluster.png 200w,\n/static/eeccf579d1262b683b0e39adc7228c26/e17e5/nsvscluster.png 400w,\n/static/eeccf579d1262b683b0e39adc7228c26/5a190/nsvscluster.png 800w,\n/static/eeccf579d1262b683b0e39adc7228c26/c1b63/nsvscluster.png 1200w,\n/static/eeccf579d1262b683b0e39adc7228c26/29007/nsvscluster.png 1600w,\n/static/eeccf579d1262b683b0e39adc7228c26/de766/nsvscluster.png 1838w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<h2>Cluster-Scoped Resources</h2>\n<p>The cluster-scoped resources are those where you don't specify a namespace when you create them such as nodes.</p>\n<p>To enable a user to access namespaced resources, you can use roles and role bindings. Similarly, to enable a user to access cluster-scoped resources, you can use <strong>cluster roles</strong> and <strong>cluster role bindings.</strong></p>\n<p>For example, you can create a Cluster Admin role as below that enables a user to view nodes, create, nodes, or delete nodes.</p>\n<p>To create them you can create a yaml file and define the kind as ClusterRole as below.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 54%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"clusterroles\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/9de1eae95eba8c11d60b5e51f62c23a5/5a190/clusterroles.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/9de1eae95eba8c11d60b5e51f62c23a5/772e8/clusterroles.png 200w,\n/static/9de1eae95eba8c11d60b5e51f62c23a5/e17e5/clusterroles.png 400w,\n/static/9de1eae95eba8c11d60b5e51f62c23a5/5a190/clusterroles.png 800w,\n/static/9de1eae95eba8c11d60b5e51f62c23a5/c1b63/clusterroles.png 1200w,\n/static/9de1eae95eba8c11d60b5e51f62c23a5/29007/clusterroles.png 1600w,\n/static/9de1eae95eba8c11d60b5e51f62c23a5/7970d/clusterroles.png 1908w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<p>Then, we can create another object called ClusterRoleBinding to link the ClusterRole to a user or a group.</p>\n<pre><code>kubectl create -f cluster-admin-role-rolebinding.yaml\n</code></pre>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 54.49999999999999%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"clusterrolebinding\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/7938d83c9e6a235c55a4c3d5d7f8cb0a/5a190/clusterrolebinding.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/7938d83c9e6a235c55a4c3d5d7f8cb0a/772e8/clusterrolebinding.png 200w,\n/static/7938d83c9e6a235c55a4c3d5d7f8cb0a/e17e5/clusterrolebinding.png 400w,\n/static/7938d83c9e6a235c55a4c3d5d7f8cb0a/5a190/clusterrolebinding.png 800w,\n/static/7938d83c9e6a235c55a4c3d5d7f8cb0a/c1b63/clusterrolebinding.png 1200w,\n/static/7938d83c9e6a235c55a4c3d5d7f8cb0a/29007/clusterrolebinding.png 1600w,\n/static/7938d83c9e6a235c55a4c3d5d7f8cb0a/7970d/clusterrolebinding.png 1908w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<p>Lastly, although clusterroles and bindings are usually used for cluster scopes, this is not a hard rule, and you can use them for namespaced resources as well. Once you do that, the user will have access to the resources accross all namespaces.</p>\n<h1>Review Quiz</h1>\n<p>How many ClusterRoles do you see defined in the cluster?</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-bash\">kubectl get clusterroles --no-headers | wc -l\n</code></pre>\n<p>How many ClusterRoleBindings exist on the cluster?</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-bash\">kubectl get clusterrolebindings --no-headers | wc -l\n</code></pre>\n<p>What namespace is the cluster-admin clusterrole part of?</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-bash\">kubectl api-resources --namespaced=false\n</code></pre>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 48.50000000000001%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"q3\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/a5cf2c6a10d59d1436d9c5ecf62422e5/5a190/q3.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/a5cf2c6a10d59d1436d9c5ecf62422e5/772e8/q3.png 200w,\n/static/a5cf2c6a10d59d1436d9c5ecf62422e5/e17e5/q3.png 400w,\n/static/a5cf2c6a10d59d1436d9c5ecf62422e5/5a190/q3.png 800w,\n/static/a5cf2c6a10d59d1436d9c5ecf62422e5/c1b63/q3.png 1200w,\n/static/a5cf2c6a10d59d1436d9c5ecf62422e5/29007/q3.png 1600w,\n/static/a5cf2c6a10d59d1436d9c5ecf62422e5/b4904/q3.png 1768w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<p>What user/groups are the cluster-admin role bound to?\nThe ClusterRoleBinding for the role is with the same name.</p>\n<pre><code>kubectl describe clusterrolebinding cluster-admin\n</code></pre>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 36%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"q4\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/cf822d30b5d2f75f444bcca85a302d60/5a190/q4.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/cf822d30b5d2f75f444bcca85a302d60/772e8/q4.png 200w,\n/static/cf822d30b5d2f75f444bcca85a302d60/e17e5/q4.png 400w,\n/static/cf822d30b5d2f75f444bcca85a302d60/5a190/q4.png 800w,\n/static/cf822d30b5d2f75f444bcca85a302d60/c1b63/q4.png 1200w,\n/static/cf822d30b5d2f75f444bcca85a302d60/203d3/q4.png 1322w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<p>What level of permission does the cluster-admin role grant?<br>\nInspect the cluster-admin role's privileges.</p>\n<pre><code>kubectl describe clusterrole cluster-admin\n</code></pre>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 30%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"q5\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/e856bcc41dcece569f2535be47c0ac32/5a190/q5.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/e856bcc41dcece569f2535be47c0ac32/772e8/q5.png 200w,\n/static/e856bcc41dcece569f2535be47c0ac32/e17e5/q5.png 400w,\n/static/e856bcc41dcece569f2535be47c0ac32/5a190/q5.png 800w,\n/static/e856bcc41dcece569f2535be47c0ac32/c1b63/q5.png 1200w,\n/static/e856bcc41dcece569f2535be47c0ac32/8affb/q5.png 1254w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<p>A new user michelle joined the team. She will be focusing on the nodes in the cluster. Create the required ClusterRoles and ClusterRoleBindings so she gets access to the nodes.</p>\n<p>michelle.yaml</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-yaml\">---\nkind: ClusterRole\napiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\nmetadata:\n  name: node-admin\nrules:\n- apiGroups: [\"\"]\n  resources: [\"nodes\"]\n  verbs: [\"get\", \"watch\", \"list\", \"create\", \"delete\"]\n\n---\nkind: ClusterRoleBinding\napiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\nmetadata:\n  name: michelle-binding\nsubjects:\n- kind: User\n  name: michelle\n  apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\nroleRef:\n  kind: ClusterRole\n  name: node-admin\n  apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n</code></pre>\n<p>kubectl create -f michelle.yaml</p>\n<p>To check if the user has access to the nodes, you can run the following command.</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-bash\">kubectl auth can-i list nodes --as michelle\n</code></pre>"}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/kubernetes/164clusterroles/"}},"staticQueryHashes":[],"slicesMap":{}}